<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880407-0063 </DOCNO><HL> GE Gets Navy Order Totaling $87.7 Million For Targeting Gear </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GE LK GD </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Electric Co. was awarded an $87.7 million Navy contract for targeting systems used in ballistic-missile submarines.    Lockheed Corp. received Air Force contracts totaling $59.5 million for production of C-130 aircraft.    General Dynamics Corp. was given a $27.4 million Army contract for M-60 tank improvements for Saudi Arabia.    American Apparel Inc. won a $13.1 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for hot-weather coats. </TEXT></DOC>